🇺🇸American banks are overloaded with data centre financing requests. Instead of approving credit at their own risk, banks are offering “opportunities” to outside investors to share in the financing deals. 

Only 2 companies, Oracle and CoreWeave, have already borrowed hundreds of billions of dollars for data centres / AI labs. Those denied bank credit started issuing bonds privately. 

Are US banks:

A) Already smelling the bust, covering their butts;

B) Missing on the opportunity of a lifetime;

C) Other?
